    <item>
      <title>Re: Serpent of Vindication</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=6105#M6105</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I have a Serpent of Vindication, and I have absolutely NO PROBLEM whatsoever bandolier'ing it to slow and bandolier'ing it back.&amp;nbsp; Now about your arguments as to why it should be clickable from Inventory:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;You claimed that the hammer of delusions, 1.5, 2.0, tier 1 and 2 robes all are clickable from inventory.&amp;nbsp; True.&amp;nbsp; But you forgot one very important thing about them, they all have recasts on them.&amp;nbsp; If you remove the 2, 3, or at some poitns even 6 minutes it takes to recast those items, they would be must equip without a doubt.&amp;nbsp; For a mana free, 1/2 cast time, 70% slow, you can afford to bandolier it in.&amp;nbsp; Thats the price you pay for mana free and 1/2 the cast time.&amp;nbsp; There have to be some limitations.&amp;nbsp; Sony cant just make it a candy land.&amp;nbsp; That would be like saying you can have this car, and you dont even have to make any payments, we'll do that for you.&amp;nbsp; How often does that happen, never.&amp;nbsp; But how often do you hear this?&amp;nbsp; "We'll make your first 2 payments, if you put this amount down, and after that we'll match you payment for payment."&amp;nbsp; That sounds slightly more plausible (and one helluva deal I might add).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The negotiation that allows us to click those items from inventory is the fact that we cant chain click them like we can the SoV.&amp;nbsp; If we could chain cast euphoria, mana free, over and over again, that would be EXTREMELY overpowering, and in my opinion would break the game.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Bottom line, be happy that you even have the **SMURF** thing.&amp;nbsp; Its the rarest of the rare in Time.&amp;nbsp; I personally think that the 1.0 should be clickable from Inventory, but it aint going to happen.&amp;nbsp; There has to be a point where we stop demanding so many things and look at what we really have. (Not saying dont fight for what we need, but dont **SMURF** about things that dont need to be changed).&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
